description: Let's imagine that we look at the sky any August evening around six or seven in the evening, a beautiful time to observe the chaos of the sky, watch how the wind collides with the sets of ice particles that make up the clouds, although it is clear that it is mere chaos at its finest, the human being strives to find something more within these floating masses, strives to create subjective coincidences between these clouds and objects, but why? Why this insatiable need for order? Could it be that human beings need to feel that they know what they see? That he has control over what he does not understand? Or do they simply want to find comfort admiring chaos?
